GUI and Graphics
Chapters 91, 107, 136

import javax.swing
    - Contains Gui classes that help in creating Guis
    .JOptionPane
        - Creates an information Pane  -> messageDialog -> JOptionPane.ShowMessageDialog(parentComponent:,String message)
        - Creates an input pane -> InputDialog -> JOptionPane.showInputDialog(String input)
            - Returns a String



Java Coordinate System

    Point of origin (x,y)
    Height, Width
    Object postion (x,y)
    int height = getHeight();
    int width = getWidth();
 <code>
    import javax.swing.Jpanel;
    import java.awt.Graphics; // provides several methos for drawing text and shapes to the screen

        .drawLine(x1,y1,x2,y2) // Draws a line from point (x1,y1) to point (x2,y2)
        .drawRectangle(x,y,w,h) // Draws a rectangle from point (x,y) with width w and height h
        .drawOval(x,y,w,h) // Draws a oval from point (x,y) width width w and height h
        .drawPolygon(x,y,h) // Draws a polygon with points x[] y[] and # of sides h
            - x = [] , y = [] h = int number of sides
 </code>

 Create a frame to show the panel

 import javax.swing.JFrame
    - creates a window

 Colors and Decorations

 import java.awt.Color
    - Contains predefined static color objects
        eg. BLACK black, BLUE blue, CYAN, cyan
    - Definition of Colors
        - RGB (Red, Green, Blue) -> (0-255,0-255,0-255) 0 Being no Representation 255 Being maximum

    - Ways to represent the colors
        - Use Color Constructors
            public Color(int r, int g, int b);
            public Color(float r, float g, float b);
            public Color(int rgb);